1
00:00:01,909 --> 00:00:06,909
SCHOOLHOUSE. Marine schoolhouse-in-a-box.

2
00:00:06,912 --> 00:00:11,912
PME today is three disconnected systems and a tired NCO. We fold them into one.

3
00:00:11,916 --> 00:00:16,916
Four datasets. Three use cases. One on-prem stack. Three role-aware views.

4
00:00:16,922 --> 00:00:21,922
Switch to the student view — start with an egocentric tactical drill.

5
00:00:21,984 --> 00:00:26,984
Multimodal coach reads the helmet-cam frame plus the Marine's typed action.

6
00:00:26,993 --> 00:00:31,993
Switch drill — Visual ID. Drop a foreign platform image.

7
00:00:28,506 --> 00:00:34,506
Vision-language analyst writes the numbered reasoning. SENTINEL pattern.

8
00:00:34,513 --> 00:00:39,513
Switch drill — Written assignment. Logistics principles paper.

9
00:00:36,042 --> 00:00:42,542
chat_json grades each rubric criterion. 0-5 score plus narrative feedback.

10
00:00:42,551 --> 00:00:47,551
Switch role — Instructor. Same data, reshaped — cohort heatmap appears.

11
00:00:47,565 --> 00:00:52,565
Cache-first Schoolhouse Intelligence Brief. Anchored to NAVMC 3500.58.

12
00:00:52,568 --> 00:00:58,068
Switch role — School CO. Same brief reshapes to a schoolhouse health dashboard.

13
00:00:58,087 --> 00:01:03,087
Audit chain — every drill, every brief, SHA-256 chained. Privacy Act governed, not FERPA.

14
00:01:03,092 --> 00:01:08,092
Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL — PME data stays inside the SCIF.

15
00:01:08,097 --> 00:01:13,097
Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
